Description. Living animals have iridescent, dark red to purple dorsal stripes at intersegmental furrows; pigment almost black in formalin; equators non-pigmented. Length 230–283 mm (n=
3 adults
); diameter 8–10 mm at x, 11–14 mm at xx; body cylindrical in cross-section, tail narrowing abruptly in last 6 segments; 113–123 segments. First dorsal pore at 12 / 13 ; spermathecal pores one pair at 7 / 8 , 0.13 circumference apart ventrally; large indistinct pads paired in viii behind spermathecal pores; female pore single in xiv, openings of copulatory bursae paired in xviii, 0.14 circumference apart ventrally, 0–4 setae between openings. Clitellum annular, extending from xiv to xvi. Setae evenly distributed around segmental equators; 53–66 setae on vii, 48–61 setae on xx, dorsal and ventral gaps absent.

